DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$n = random(1, 4);
$m = random(5, 7);
$a = 2 * $m * $n;
$b = $m**2 - $n**2;
$c = $m**2 + $n**2;

$ans1 = $a - $b;
$ans2 = $a + $b;

$ans3 = 8 * $c**4 /3;

BEGIN_TEXT
$PAR
Consider the transformation
\( T: x = \frac{$a}{$c}u - \frac{$b}{$c}v, \ \ y = \frac{$b}{$c}u +
\frac{$a}{$c}v \)
$PAR
A. Computer the Jacobian: $BR
 \( \frac{\partial(x, y)}{\partial(u, v)} = \)
\{ ans_rule(30) \}
$PAR
B. The transformation is linear, which implies that it transforms lines into
lines.  Thus, it transforms the square \( S:-$c \leq u \leq $c, -$c \leq v \leq
$c \) into a square \( T(S) \) with vertices:
$PAR
T($c, $c) = (\{ ans_rule(20) \}, \{ ans_rule(20) \})
$PAR
T(-$c, $c) = (\{ ans_rule(20) \}, \{ ans_rule(20) \})
$PAR
T(-$c, -$c) = (\{ ans_rule(20) \}, \{ ans_rule(20) \})
$PAR
T($c, -$c) = (\{ ans_rule(20) \}, \{ ans_rule(20) \})
$PAR
C. Use the transformation \( T \) to evaluate the integral \( \int \!\!
\int_{T(S)} \ x^2 + y^2 \ {dA} \)
$PAR
\{ ans_rule(40) \}
END_TEXT
#A.
ANS(num_cmp(1));

#B.
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));

ANS(num_cmp(-$ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));

ANS(num_cmp(-$ans1));
ANS(num_cmp(-$ans2));

ANS(num_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp(-$ans1));

#C.
ANS(num_cmp($ans3));

ENDDOCUMENT();
